race.comment: FLICK THE SWITCH (6) will find this much easier than what she's been in, rounding out her last campaign with two efforts in town. She was a dominant winner at Mt Barker before that however, sitting on the speed in a similar race to this. Usually comes to hand quickly and while she hasn't trialled, this looks a very winnable race for her. TACITO (5) is another first-up today, joining the Harding stable from Victoria. He too hasn't trialled this time in work, though he's never missed the placings fresh and his form from last campaign stacks right up. Can play a major role. AVOIDANCE (3) looked good in a recent trial here and ticks a few boxes. The claim of Mahony comes in handy while he should sit on the speed from the draw. Can resume on a positive note. GIFT OF THE HEART (4) is a track and trip winner previously and should be fitter for a recent trial where he was around some handy types. BLUE LINE (7) wasn't beaten far first-up and the rise in trip suits.
